In the segmentation task, the feature maps need to be normalized to have equal dimensions by the downsampling block before fusion. Feature maps are downsampled to a fixed length by a novel mechanism shown in Eq. 1, which is a trade-off between performance and complexity. Contrary to convolution based down sampling methods [21], our down sampling block is parameter-free. Average pooling is exploited for less information loss during downsampling, while max-pooling highlights the discriminative features in the feature maps.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
